                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.506 Manchuria/24: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-30T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 30, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>262. Your 517, October 27, noon. The Department concurs in the recommendation
                    contained in the last paragraph that at this time no action be taken.</p>
                <p>Please continue to keep the Department informed of developments, including the
                    attitude of other interested governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
